# SQL Day 2

## 🎯 Today's Mission

Build the foundation of GlobalMart's customer database.

---

## 🏢 Business Scenario

You have joined GlobalMart Logistics & Retail as a Junior Business Analyst.

Your manager asks you to create the company's first customer database.

---

## 🧠 Architecture Learned

- MySQL Server
- Database
- Tables
- Rows
- Columns
- How Workbench connects to MySQL Server

---

## ⚙️ SQL Commands Learned

```sql
CREATE DATABASE GlobalMart;

USE GlobalMart;

CREATE TABLE Customers(
    CustomerID INT,
    Name VARCHAR(50),
    City VARCHAR(50),
    Age INT
);

SHOW TABLES;
```

---

## 💡 What Actually Happened?

When I executed `CREATE DATABASE GlobalMart;`

- MySQL Server received my SQL command.
- It created a new database.
- The database was registered inside MySQL.
- MySQL Workbench displayed it in the Schemas panel.

When I created the Customers table,

- MySQL created a table inside GlobalMart.
- The table currently has columns only.
- No rows (customer data) exist yet.

---

## 📊 Project Progress

```
MySQL Server
│
└── GlobalMart
      │
      └── Customers
```

---

## 📝 Reflection

Today I understood the difference between:

- MySQL Server
- MySQL Workbench
- SQL

I also learned that a table is only a structure.

The actual customer data will be inserted later.

